  "text_preview": "\"left\" ASL American Sign Language ASL University ► left Move the an \"L\" hand to the left. I tend to just use my dominant hand (I'm right handed) for this sign. I've noticed though that lots of right-handed folks use their left hand to sign LEFT. LEFT: (as in the direction) For \"left\" as in the past tense of \"leave\" -- see \" LEAVE \" ASL University ► You can learn American Sign Language (ASL) online at American Sign Language University ™ ASL resources by Lifeprint.com © Dr. William Vicars American Sign Language University ™ ASL resources by Lifeprint.com © Dr. William Vicars You can learn American Sign Language (ASL) online at American Sign Language University ™ ASL resources by Lifeprint.com © Dr. William Vicars"
